2
00:00:47,660 --> 00:00:51,250
Some people say that fairies are the stuff of fantasy.
有些人说仙子是虚幻之物

3
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:56,720
They think the world is just what you can touch and hear and see,
他们认为世界上只有你能摸到、听到、看到的东西

4
00:00:56,840 --> 00:01:00,530
while others say the tales and legends cannot be dismissed.
而另一些人说并不能排除传说和神话的可能

5
00:01:01,170 --> 00:01:05,840
They believe with all their hearts that fairies truly do exist.
他们笃信仙子真的存在

6
00:01:07,780 --> 00:01:12,180
Through out all time, human beings and fairies never met,
从古至今 人类从来没有遇到过仙子

7
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:18,520
till one very special summer that we shall not soon forget.
直到一个非常特殊的难忘的夏天

8
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:29,620
小叮当: 夏日风暴

9
00:01:29,900 --> 00:01:35,930
Life is rising up Surging forth in all directions
万物生长 纵情歌唱

10
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:41,910
Every little buttercup Is reaching out to find connections
黄花遍野

11
00:01:41,980 --> 00:01:45,070
Every blade of grass Will touch the sunlight
绿草沐阳

12
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:48,580
The rain will touch the ground
雨润沃土

13
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:53,450
Growing greener than it was before
幼芽新张

14
00:01:55,390 --> 00:02:01,130
Bees are droning by Spider silk is softly spinning
蜜蜂飞鸣 蜘蛛织网

15
00:02:01,230 --> 00:02:06,970
Not a cloud in the sky You know it's only the beginning
万里无云 晴日方长

16
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:13,770
Every little blossom, every flower Flings its petals wide
花朵怒放

17
00:02:13,850 --> 00:02:18,480
As the season comes round Once more
夏季回来

18
00:02:19,850 --> 00:02:22,650
Hey, Tink! You ready for your first summer on the mainland?
嘿 叮当 这是你在这片大陆的第一个夏天 准备好了吗?

19
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:25,920
Absolutely! It's so beautiful out here.
当然 这里真美丽

20
00:02:26,020 --> 00:02:28,460
I can't believe we get to stay for the whole season.
真不敢相信 我们要在这儿过整个夏天

21
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:31,930
Well, what are we waiting for? Race you down!
好呀 那还等什么? 下降了!

22
00:02:33,030 --> 00:02:39,330
The breeze is blowing light and sweet The grass, a carpet at your feet
空气清新 绿草如茵

23
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:43,700
Catch the colors Feel the heat of the sun
满目缤纷 周身暖阳

24
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:51,980
All the sparrows in the dell Swirling round like a carousel
燕舞幽谷 盘旋喧嚣

25
00:02:52,180 --> 00:02:55,980
Singing loud enough to tell everyone
歌向四野

26
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:57,040
Hi, guys.
嗨 伙计们

27
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:58,880
Summer's just begun
夏季来临

28
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:05,030
Summer's just begun
夏季来临

29
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:10,860
There it is, Tink. Fairy camp!
我们到了 叮当 仙子园

30
00:03:10,970 --> 00:03:13,960
All the winters, all the springs
冬寒春暖

31
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:17,140
Lead us here on fairy wings
仙翼随风

32
00:03:17,210 --> 00:03:21,370
A season of a thousand things To be done
万事待兴

33
00:03:21,980 --> 00:03:23,710
Summer's just begun
夏季来临

34
00:03:28,420 --> 00:03:30,350
Summer's just begun
夏季来临

35
00:03:33,430 --> 00:03:34,720
Hiya, Cheese!
嘿 奶酪!

36
00:03:34,830 --> 00:03:36,090
Summer's just begun
夏季来临

37
00:03:36,190 --> 00:03:38,890
- Did you have a nice flight? - Incoming!
- 飞行还好吗? - 来了!

38
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,490
Keep her level! Keep her level!
保持水平 保持水平

39
00:03:40,670 --> 00:03:42,430
Gear it down, Bobble!
稳住 波波!

40
00:03:42,530 --> 00:03:44,000
Oh-ho!
噢...啊!

41
00:03:44,070 --> 00:03:46,940
- Smashing landing, Clanky. - Thank you, Bobble
- 硬着陆 柯朗 - 谢谢 波波

42
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:49,840
Guys, I think you may have over-packed.
伙计们 我觉得你们可能超重了

43
00:03:50,180 --> 00:03:52,940
- Come on, Tink. Let's go inside. - Inside?
- 来吧 叮当 我们进去 - 进去?

44
00:03:53,510 --> 00:03:56,410
Tink, fairy camp isn't out here in the open.
叮当 这个外面的野地不是仙子园

45
00:03:56,550 --> 00:03:58,410
We need to stay hidden from the humans.
我们要躲着人类

46
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:00,510
- We do? - Uh. Yeah.
- 非要这样吗? - 呃 是的

47
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:03,190
That's why fairy camp is in here.
所以仙子园要在这里面

48
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:15,760
Cicadas, one at a time. You, you and you. You, too.
知了们 一次一个 你 你 还有你

49
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:20,900
Wow. lt's like all of Pixie Hollow under one tree!
哇噢 这真像整个精灵谷放在了一颗树下

50
00:04:34,450 --> 00:04:35,440
Blaze!
亮亮!

51
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:36,980
Hmm?
嗯

52
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:07,310
The Queen Anne's lace is looking beautiful.
安妮女王的蕾丝真好看

53
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:10,580
- How are the looms working? - Fine, thanks to you, Tink.
- 这纺织机正常吗? - 挺好的 谢谢 叮当

54
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:15,460
Next. Next. Next.
下一个 下一个 下一个

55
00:05:15,530 --> 00:05:19,020
- Hows the bee-liner working? - Like a dream Tink. Thanks
- 这蜜蜂画机怎么样呀? - 和梦想的一样好 叮当 谢谢

56
00:05:19,130 --> 00:05:21,460
Great. Need any help with that wagon?
那好 那辆货车要帮忙吗?

57
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:23,020
No, thanks. She's running fine.
不用 谢谢 她工作正常

58
00:05:23,130 --> 00:05:25,000
Okay. Glad to hear it.
好的 那就好

59
00:05:26,370 --> 00:05:28,430
Here's the first week's supply.
这是第一周的给养

60
00:05:28,510 --> 00:05:32,770
Okay, I'm off. I gotta go deliver pixie dust to the other fairy camps,
好的 我出去了 我要去把仙粉分发给别的仙子园

61
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:35,280
but I'll see you in a couple days.
要几天后再见了

62
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:39,140
Oh, and Tink! Don't worry. You'll find something to fix.
噢 叮当 别担心 你会找到东西修理的

63
00:05:41,150 --> 00:05:42,480
I hope so.
但愿如此

64
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:45,210
In the meantime I need to go find some lost things.
现在 我要去找一些人们的弃物了

65
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:47,450
Hold on, little miss spare parts.
等一下 小缺心眼

66
00:05:47,530 --> 00:05:50,150
You're not going near the human house, are you?
你别去人类的房子附近 你会吗?

67
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:54,720
- There's a human house? - No! I mean, yes, but no.
- 那里有人类的房子? - 不! 我是说 是的 也不是

68
00:05:54,830 --> 00:05:57,630
- We stay away from humans. - Oh, Iridessa!
- 我们要与人类保持距离 - 噢 伊瑞蒂瑟

69
00:05:59,140 --> 00:06:04,580
- Tinker Bell knows that, don't you? - Define "stay away"
- 叮当是知道的了 对吧? - 什么叫"保持距离"

70
00:06:04,710 --> 00:06:07,300
It's gonna be a long summer.
呃 这将是一个难熬的夏天

71
00:06:07,380 --> 00:06:08,500
Grouchy.
生气了

72
00:06:08,810 --> 00:06:12,980
- Oh, that's just Vidia being Vidia. - No, the air. It smells...
- 噢 维蒂亚就是这样 - 不 这气氛 闻起来...

73
00:06:13,050 --> 00:06:14,580
...grouchy.
...可不怎么样

74
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:18,050
- We might be in for a storm. - Come on Sil.
- 暴风雨要来了 - 得了吧 秀尔

75
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:23,230
The sun is shining, the air is warm. It's a beautiful day. Nothing's gonna...
阳光明媚 暖洋洋的 是个好天 没事的...

76
00:07:11,880 --> 00:07:13,810
Tinker Bell.
这个叮当

77
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:30,060
Thank goodness we're here, Father. It's just like I remember it.
谢天谢地我们到家了 爸爸 和我记得的一样

78
00:07:30,130 --> 00:07:31,960
Wel, of course, my darling.
是的 当然 我亲爱的

79
00:07:32,060 --> 00:07:34,790
Look at the creek and the woods and the meadow
瞧这小河、大树 还有草地

80
00:07:36,070 --> 00:07:38,560
Oh! I wish it was summer all year long!
噢! 真希望全年都是夏天!

81
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:41,000
Yes, Lizzy.
是的 莉兹

82
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:07,320
Tinker Bell, what are you doing here?
叮当 你在那里做什么?

83
00:08:07,430 --> 00:08:11,530
Vidia, this is amazing! It's a carriage that moves by itself!
维蒂亚 真奇妙 这是一个自己走的车!

84
00:08:11,940 --> 00:08:13,840
There's no horse. Seriously, look.
真的不用马 瞧

85
00:08:13,940 --> 00:08:16,030
- Do you see a horse up there? - Uh, No.
- 你看到这里有马吗? - 呃 没有

86
00:08:16,140 --> 00:08:20,200
It'is a horseless carriage! And do you want to know how it works?
这是一个无马车! 你想知道他是怎么走吗?

87
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:22,110
- Not really. - So do I.
- 不怎么想 - 可是我想

88
00:08:22,310 --> 00:08:26,550
I think those wheels back there move because this chain thing rotates
我觉得后面的那些轮子动 是因为这个链着的东西在转

89
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:29,610
And I think what rotates the chain is this big...
我还觉得转这个链子的是这个大...

90
00:08:29,690 --> 00:08:33,380
I don't care Tinker Bell. You shouldn't be this close to the human house.
管他呢 叮当 你不应当离人类的房子这么近

91
00:08:33,490 --> 00:08:35,290
What if they see us?
如果他们看到我们 会怎样?

92
00:08:38,630 --> 00:08:42,120
Will you stop flitting around in there? This is serious!
你别在那里飞来飞去了 听到吗

93
00:08:42,670 --> 00:08:46,300
You know what, Vidia? I think this powers the whole thing!
你知道吗 维蒂亚? 我觉得是这家伙给整个车提供动力

94
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:54,640
This, my dear, is exactly why tinkers shouldn't come to the mainland. They...
天呀 这就是为什么修理匠不应该 派到这个大陆来 他们...

95
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:57,740
Let me know if this does anything.
让我看看这是做什么的

96
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:04,660
Well, anything? Vidia, you're all wet.
好了 有什么动静吗? 维蒂亚 你都湿透了

97
00:09:06,090 --> 00:09:07,560
You don't say.
你还说

98
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:11,060
Father, Father Father! Can we bring our tea and scones outside
爸爸 爸爸 爸爸! 我们可以把茶点拿到外面吗?

99
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:12,650
and have them here in the garden?
在花园里面吃?

100
00:09:12,730 --> 00:09:15,320
- It would be just like a little picnic. - Not just now, Lizzy.
- 就像野餐一样 - 现在不行 莉兹

101
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:18,100
I still have to get the trunk unpacked and the house settled
我还在卸行李 拾掇房子

102
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:21,430
Father, look! What a magnificent butterfly.
爸爸 看 多么特别的一只蝴蝶

103
00:09:23,610 --> 00:09:28,200
My word. Absolutely astonishing.
额的神呀 绝对怪异

104
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:31,370
It's so beautiful. What kind of butterfly is it?
它真漂亮 它是什么品种?

105
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:36,010
Well, judging from the epidermal membrane, it's cleary an apatura iris,
好的 根据外形来看 它显然是紫闪蛱蝶

106
00:09:36,090 --> 00:09:39,520
but the wings have two entirely different patterns.
但这两个翅膀呈现完全不同的图案

107
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:42,080
Well, that's neary impossible.
当然 这几乎不可能

108
00:09:42,190 --> 00:09:45,690
Well, I guess that's just the way the fairies decided to paint it.
好吧 我猜是仙子们决定这么画的

109
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:46,750
Hmm?
嗯?

110
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:48,860
Lizzy, faires do not paint butterfly wings
莉兹 蝴蝶翅膀不是仙子们画的

111
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:52,530
because, as you know, fairies are not real.
因为你知道的 仙子并不是真的

112
00:09:52,770 --> 00:09:53,760
- Hmm! - Ugh!
- 嗯! - 呃!

113
00:09:53,870 --> 00:09:56,100
But of course they are. The proof is right here.
可他们当然是真的 这就是证明

114
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:59,770
- Their paint dripped all over its wing. - Really, darling.
- 他们的颜料滴在这整个翅膀上了 - 是吗 亲爱的

115
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:03,870
Rational people consider a belief in fairies to be quite foolish.
理性的人们相信仙子是相当愚蠢的

116
00:10:04,050 --> 00:10:05,110
The wings are so fresh.
这翅膀可真鲜见

117
00:10:05,220 --> 00:10:06,440
What are you doing?
你在做什么?

118
00:10:06,550 --> 00:10:08,610
Its chrysalis must have been in the meadow.
它的茧一定是在草地上

119
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:11,420
The meadow? Father wait!
草地? 爸爸! 等等!

120
00:10:13,220 --> 00:10:16,130
That's where I'm going. Would you like to come?
我正要去那里 你也来吗?

121
00:10:16,230 --> 00:10:18,390
Not now, Lizzy. I have to update my field journal.
现在不行 莉兹 我要去整理我的野外日志

122
00:10:18,460 --> 00:10:21,090
My interview at the museum is tomorrow night
明天晚上我要去博物馆开会

123
00:10:21,170 --> 00:10:24,570
You're going back already? We just got here.
你刚回来呀 我们才到这里

124
00:10:25,570 --> 00:10:30,060
I know, sweetheart, and I'm very sorry. But I'll only be gone for the day.
我知道 乖乖 真对不起 但我只是白天到那里去

125
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:34,340
Mrs. Perkins will look after you, and I'll be back in time to tuck you in.
伯金斯太太会照顾你的 我也会按时回来送你上床睡觉

126
00:10:34,450 --> 00:10:36,850
- Promise? - I promise.
- 一定? - 我肯定

127
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:40,650
- Okay. - That's a good girl.
- 那好吧 - 真是好囡囡

128
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,030
All clear!
安全了!

129
00:10:54,670 --> 00:10:55,790
Come on, Vidia.
来呀 维蒂亚

130
00:10:55,870 --> 00:11:00,700
- I can't fly. My wings are wet. - Oh! That's right. Sorry.
- 我飞不动 我的翅膀湿了 - 噢! 是呀 真抱歉

131
00:11:01,030 --> 00:11:04,100
Guess you'll have to walk back.
我想你只好走回去了

132
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:09,440
But don't worry, I'll keep you company. Actually, it might be nice
不过 别担心 我会陪你的 实际上 这样可能更好

133
00:11:13,350 --> 00:11:16,980
Or not So, I think I figured out the carriage.
也许不好 那我就明白这个车了

134
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:19,350
Those bottles of goop must keep it running smoothly,
这些粘湿的东西一定是用来保持平顺运行的

135
00:11:19,460 --> 00:11:21,550
like snail slime, you know?
就像蜗牛的粘液 你知道吗?

136
00:11:21,660 --> 00:11:25,120
Hate to see the size of the snail that stuff comes from. And at first...
那东西如果来自蜗牛 可蜗牛太小了 那么 最初...

137
00:12:02,970 --> 00:12:06,470
Here's your house, little fairies. Wherever you are.
小仙子 不管你们在哪里 这是你的房子

138
00:12:09,740 --> 00:12:13,010
Hmm Just needs a little something more.
嗯 还少了一点东西

139
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:19,940
But I haven't quite figured out what that sparky wire does.
但我还不知道那个闪电的线是做什么的

140
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:23,680
Hey! Maybe the whole carriage runs on lightning!
哎 也许整个车子是靠闪电运行

141
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:31,290
Are those wet wings still bugging you? Here, Vidia, let me help you.
你的湿翅膀还不能用吗? 这样 维蒂亚 我来帮你

142
00:12:32,760 --> 00:12:36,600
Tinker Bell, maybe if you spent less tme causing disasters,
小叮当 也许你可以少闯点祸

143
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:40,360
you wouldn't have to help everybody so much.
这样你也用不着这么帮别人

144
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:46,700
- Hmm. The truth hurts, doesn't it? - Look! We can use these back at camp!
- 怎么这话伤着你了? - 瞧! 我们可以在仙子园用这东西

145
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:51,540
Wow. These'll be perfect for the new wagon prototype I've been working on.
哇噢 这些可用在我做的新货车原型上

146
00:12:51,620 --> 00:12:54,450
Here. I bet if I took two or three and tied them together,
拿着 我打赌只要我们用两三个固定在一起

147
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:57,110
I could make one really strong wheel!
我就可以做一个真正坚固的轮子!

148
00:12:57,220 --> 00:13:01,390
It's a good thing we were walking or we might never have seen these.
我们走回来可真好 要不我们就找不到这些东西了

149
00:13:01,460 --> 00:13:03,650
Vidia, where are your buttons?
维蒂亚 给你的钮扣呢?

150
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:08,160
Tinker Bell, am not carrying this human junk back to camp.
小叮当 我不能把这些人类的垃圾带回仙子园

151
00:13:17,270 --> 00:13:19,070
- Let's go! - Let's go!
- 快跑! - 快跑!

152
00:13:20,670 --> 00:13:22,450
"欢迎仙子"

153
00:13:22,450 --> 00:13:26,680
Tinker Bell, we're not supposed to go near human houses.
叮当! 我们不能靠近人类的房子

154
00:13:26,780 --> 00:13:28,180
This isn't a human house.
这不是人类的房子

155
00:13:28,290 --> 00:13:29,480
They're a lot bigger.
那要大得多

156
00:13:29,590 --> 00:13:32,180
Besides, the sign says, "Fairies welcome."
再说 牌子上写了"欢迎仙子"

157
00:13:32,290 --> 00:13:34,950
Who do you think wrote it? Humans!
你以为是谁写的? 人类!

158
00:13:35,380 --> 00:13:36,950
"仙子邮箱"

159
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:39,790
Tinker Bell, you're not going in there.
叮当! 你不能进去

160
00:13:41,230 --> 00:13:45,160
Please tell me you're not going in there! She went in there.
快说呀 你不会进去的 她进去了

161
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:06,360
Tinker Bell! Don't eat that! This could be a trap.
叮当! 别吃! 可能有诈

162
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:09,570
Come on, Vidia. It's perfectly safe.
得了吧 维蒂亚 这很安全

163
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:11,070
Oh, really?
噢! 真的吗?

164
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:19,980
- Oh, Vidia - Huh! Not so safe now, is it?
- 噢! 维蒂亚 - 哈! 现在不那么安全了 是吗?

165
00:14:20,420 --> 00:14:23,190
Nice try, Vidia, but you re not scaring me.
干得不错 维蒂亚 但我不怕

166
00:14:23,260 --> 00:14:24,880
Gosh, this thing is amazing.
天啊! 这东西真奇妙

167
00:14:24,990 --> 00:14:27,020
You just don't know when to stop, do you?
你没完了 是吧?

168
00:14:30,830 --> 00:14:33,320
Oh, no. Tink! Someone's coming!
噢! 不 叮当 有人过来了

169
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:36,600
The door is stuck!
这门粘住了!

170
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:38,730
Come on, Vidia You can do better than that.
得了吧 维蒂亚 能不能换个招呀

171
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:41,170
- Tink! - I wonder what this part does.
- 叮当 - 我来看看这个零件是做什么的

172
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:44,210
Tink! I'm serious! Get out of there!
叮当! 是真的 赶快出来

173
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:46,210
Just a second. Just a second.
等一下 等一下

174
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:59,730
Vidia? Vidia?
维蒂亚? 维蒂亚!

175
00:15:03,030 --> 00:15:05,930
Oh Vidia, come on. Open the door. You had your little...
噢 维蒂亚 帮帮忙 把门打开 你有点...

176
00:15:11,210 --> 00:15:13,730
Oh, no. What have I done?
噢! 不 我干了什么呀?

177
00:15:14,380 --> 00:15:17,710
Vidia? Okay, not funny anymore.
维蒂亚? 好了 这不好玩了

178
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:25,880
A fairy!
仙子!

179
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:32,390
It's a real fairy!
是一个真的仙子哎!

180
00:15:37,830 --> 00:15:39,960
Father! Father!
爸爸! 爸爸!

181
00:15:46,170 --> 00:15:47,400
Father!
爸爸!

182
00:15:58,590 --> 00:16:01,110
- Father! Father, Father! - Yes, Lizzy.
- 爸爸! 爸爸! 爸爸! - 我在这 莉兹

183
00:16:01,420 --> 00:16:03,250
You're never going to believe what I found.
你一定不相信我看到了什么

184
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:07,190
- Maybe later, Lizzy. - But Father, Father, Father,
- 等一下 莉兹 - 可是...爸爸! 爸爸! 爸爸!

185
00:16:07,290 --> 00:16:08,990
- Father Father - Just a moment, dear.
- 爸爸! 爸爸! - 等一下 亲爱的

186
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:12,200
- I'm very busy with my project. - Yes, but Father!
- 我在做事 我很忙 - 我知道 可是爸爸!

187
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,590
- Father! - Lizzy, please.
- 爸爸! - 莉兹 好了

188
00:16:13,670 --> 00:16:17,430
I must add this extraordinary discovery to my field journal.
我一定要把这个惊人的发现加入我的野外日志

189
00:16:17,510 --> 00:16:19,030
And here t is.
就是这个

190
00:16:20,610 --> 00:16:23,200
Is that the butterfly we were looking at earlier?
这不是我们先前看到的那只蝴蝶吗?

191
00:16:23,310 --> 00:16:26,010
Yes. Quite a specimen isn't it?
正是 很好的一个标本 不是吗?

192
00:16:26,110 --> 00:16:28,270
You re not going to take it to London, are you?
你不会把它带到伦敦去吧 会吗?

193
00:16:28,350 --> 00:16:29,370
Yes of course.
会的! 当然要带去

194
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:31,140
The board of trustees would never believe me
要是理事会不亲眼看到

195
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:32,450
if they didn't see it themselves.
是不会相信的

196
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:35,180
Now I'm sure to get that curatorship at the museum
现在 我能得到博物馆研究员职位了

197
00:16:35,290 --> 00:16:37,450
Besides, as a member of the scientific community,
还有科学院院士

198
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:41,520
I'm obligated to share significant findings like this with my colleagues.
我也有义务与我的同事分享这非凡的发现

199
00:16:41,630 --> 00:16:45,860
I know it's unfortunate for the specimen, but really, there is no otherway.
我知道对这个标本这很不幸 但我也实在没别的办法

200
00:16:45,970 --> 00:16:48,130
Now, dear. What did you want me to see?
现在 亲爱的 你要让我看什么?

201
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:49,290
Uh ...
呃...

202
00:16:49,370 --> 00:16:50,740
Never mind.
没什么

203
00:17:13,930 --> 00:17:15,690
Where have you gone?
你跑到哪里去了?

204
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:34,180
Mr Twitches, no! Out! Out with you!
抽疯先生 不! 出去! 你出去!

205
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:39,450
Mr. Twitches!
抽疯先生!

206
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:47,460
Bad cat! No, no, no!
坏猫! 不 不 不!

207
00:17:51,370 --> 00:17:53,230
Don't worry, little fairy.
别害怕 小仙子

208
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:56,060
Mr. Twitches won't bother you as long as you're in there.
你在那里面 抽疯先生就抓不到你了

209
00:17:57,540 --> 00:18:00,440
Naughty cat! You're going outside.
顽皮猫! 你应该到外面去

210
00:19:19,790 --> 00:19:21,450
Tnker Bell's been captured by humans!
叮当被人类抓去了

211
00:19:22,790 --> 00:19:23,980
- Oh, no. - What happened? Is she okay?
- 噢 不 - 发生什么事了 她还好吗?

212
00:19:24,060 --> 00:19:25,320
- Is she all right? - What's this? Tinker Bell?
- 她还好吗? - 怎么了? 叮当?

213
00:19:25,390 --> 00:19:26,860
- What happened, Vidia? - Is she hurt?
- 发生什么了? 维蒂亚? - 她受伤了吗?

214
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:30,490
Tinker Bell went into this little house in the meadow and couldn't get out.
叮当进到草地上的那个小房子里 出不来了

215
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:32,360
The door got jammed.
门被卡住了

216
00:19:32,630 --> 00:19:35,360
Then this human came from out of nowhere and snatched her up,
后来那个人不知从哪里冒出来 把她带走了

217
00:19:35,470 --> 00:19:38,370
but I know where she is. We have to hurry and save her.
但我知道她在哪里 我们要赶快去救她

218
00:19:38,470 --> 00:19:40,800
Then we better leave right away!
我们最好现在就去

219
00:19:45,310 --> 00:19:47,210
Sil, do you think the storm will pass soon?
秀尔 你觉得暴雨会很快过去吗?

220
00:19:47,310 --> 00:19:49,870
No, it looks like it's gonna get stronger.
不会 看起来它越下越大了

221
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:52,040
Well, there's gotta be some way to get to Tink.
好吧 一定有办法去救叮当

222
00:19:52,150 --> 00:19:55,140
We can't fly in the rain and the meadow's already flooded.
我们不能在雨中飞行 而那个草地已经淹了

223
00:19:55,220 --> 00:19:56,990
Maybe we don't have to fly.
可能我们不一定要飞

224
00:19:57,060 --> 00:20:01,150
If we get some big leaves and sew them togetherwth stem twine...
如果我们用一些大叶子 再用草绳缝起来...

225
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:03,590
And miter-cut some twigs for the sub-flooring.
然后斜切一些树枝做甲板

226
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:05,060
Acorns as counterweights.
用橡果做压仓

227
00:20:05,170 --> 00:20:07,500
Some quick-dry maple sap as reinforcement.
涂上一些速干的枫树汁来加固

228
00:20:07,570 --> 00:20:09,060
What are you two talking about?
你们俩在说什么呀?

229
00:20:09,170 --> 00:20:12,260
- We're gonna build a boat! - We're gonna build a boat!
- 我们要造一条船! - 我们要造一条船!

230
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:25,520
- More mushroom caps, p ease! - Here we go.
- 多搞些蘑菇帽! - 这就是了

231
00:20:27,350 --> 00:20:30,880
This one goes there. That one goes there. Right?
这个放那里 那个放那里 对吗?

232
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:34,420
Righty-o, Bobble.
完全正确 波波

233
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:50,610
- Right, more reeds over here. - This thing had better work.
- 对 在这多放些芦苇 - 这东西最好管用

234
00:20:50,710 --> 00:20:52,080
Give me the sap.
把树汁给我

235
00:20:52,150 --> 00:20:54,940
You dip it in this way and give it a big slap like so.
你要这样泡着它 再这样拍它

236
00:20:57,220 --> 00:21:00,080
Ow. Ow. Ow.
噢 噢 噢

237
00:21:00,150 --> 00:21:02,590
Come on. Come on. Let's get going.
来吧 来吧 让我们来

238
00:21:05,130 --> 00:21:07,560
There you go. Now you're talking!
做好了真是好办法!

239
00:21:14,570 --> 00:21:16,000
It's working!
它动了!

240
00:21:24,310 --> 00:21:25,780
Well, this is it.
好了 就是它了

241
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:30,640
Hey, faith...
嘿 信念...

242
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:32,250
Trust ...
信任...

243
00:21:32,320 --> 00:21:33,910
- And pixie dust. - Pixie dust.
还有仙粉

244
00:21:40,260 --> 00:21:42,090
Come on. Come on.
来吧 来吧

245
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:49,830
Hello.
哈喽

246
00:21:53,940 --> 00:21:57,670
You don't have to be scared. I'm very nice
你不用害怕 我很好的

247
00:22:01,450 --> 00:22:03,040
You're so ittle.
你这么小

248
00:22:03,650 --> 00:22:07,610
Your dress is very leafy. Did you make it yourself?
你的裙子真像树叶一样 是你自己做的吗?

249
00:22:08,390 --> 00:22:11,480
I like your wings. They're like sparkly lace.
我喜欢你的翅膀 他们就像闪亮的蕾丝

250
00:22:12,030 --> 00:22:14,050
Your hair must be so soft.
你的头发一定很软

251
00:22:16,330 --> 00:22:20,860
Are you hungry? Maybe not. That's okay.
你饿吗? 可能不饿 没关系

252
00:22:21,140 --> 00:22:23,630
I don't like some kinds of food, either.
我也不喜欢某些食物!

253
00:22:25,510 --> 00:22:26,630
Oh!
噢!

254
00:22:26,710 --> 00:22:29,700
I'm so sorry. Where are my manners?
真对不起 这真没礼貌

255
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:32,680
There you go.
出来吧

256
00:22:39,990 --> 00:22:45,480
Wait! Wait! Wait! No, please! I'm not going to hurt you!
等下! 等下! 等下! 请别那样! 我没想伤害你!

257
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:51,160
Don't be afraid I just want to be your friend!
别害怕 我只想和你做朋友

258
00:22:53,170 --> 00:22:58,000
I really won't hurt you. I just love fairies.
我真没想伤害你 我只是喜欢仙子

259
00:22:59,210 --> 00:23:02,180
I've been drawing fairies all my life. See?
我整天画仙子 瞧

260
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:07,340
I drew that one when I was three but I did that green one last week.
这个是我三岁画的 那个绿的是上星期画的

261
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:10,510
I think it's much better.
我想这个画得好多了

262
00:23:11,090 --> 00:23:14,850
I even started to paint with the watercolors Father gave me.
我画这个已经用了爸爸给我的水彩

263
00:23:16,620 --> 00:23:19,460
Is it true that some fairies paint butterfly wings?
有些仙子会给蝴蝶画翅膀 是真的吗?

264
00:23:22,360 --> 00:23:23,690
I knew it!
我就知道!

265
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:26,930
These are some of my favorite drawings.
这些是我最喜欢的画

266
00:23:27,130 --> 00:23:28,690
This is a water fairy.
这个是水仙子

267
00:23:28,770 --> 00:23:32,030
- You can tell because her skin is blue. - Blue?
- 你看她水蓝色的皮肤就知道了 - 蓝色的? !

268
00:23:32,210 --> 00:23:35,440
And here is a candy fa ry living in a lollipop tree
那个是糖果仙子 住在棒棒糖树上

269
00:23:35,540 --> 00:23:37,480
Do all fairies live in trees made of sweets?
仙子们都住在糖做的树上吗?

270
00:23:40,210 --> 00:23:43,380
Really? What about fairy circles?
是吗? 那仙界是什么模样的?

271
00:23:45,550 --> 00:23:48,210
Well, I hear that if a person steps in one,
我听说如果一个人进入仙界

272
00:23:48,290 --> 00:23:51,950
a fairy has to grant them three wishes from their magic bag.
仙子会用他们的魔法袋 让他许三个愿望

273
00:23:52,730 --> 00:23:56,290
But if they don't, they turn into a pile of del cious sugar,
但如果他不要 就会得到一大堆好吃的糖果

274
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:58,090
- and then younger fairies - Wait. Wait a minute.
- 等等等一下 - 然后年轻的仙子们...

275
00:23:58,170 --> 00:24:00,630
...must try and turn them back into... - Where are you getting all this?
- 你从哪里知道的这些 - 会要试着把他们...

276
00:24:02,940 --> 00:24:06,430
You jingle when you talk, like a little bell!
你说话时发出叮铃声 像个小铃当

277
00:24:06,740 --> 00:24:08,830
So thats how fairies speak.
仙子们都这样说话吗?

278
00:24:10,580 --> 00:24:14,070
So what do you think of my fairies? Oh! And my fairy house!
那么 你觉得我画的仙子怎么样? 噢! 还有我的仙子房子!

279
00:24:17,350 --> 00:24:19,410
It got a little shaken up.
它被摇得有点散了

280
00:24:24,660 --> 00:24:26,520
Did you make this?
是你做的吗?

281
00:24:26,630 --> 00:24:28,420
I don't know what you're saying.
我听不到你说什么?

282
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:38,670
Oh. Did I make the fairy house? Yes, I did. Do you like it?
噢是我做的仙子房子吗? 是的 是我做的 你喜欢吗?

283
00:24:42,380 --> 00:24:44,710
Oh. The door's stuck.
噢 门卡住了

284
00:24:51,690 --> 00:24:54,850
Well, you're quite the little tinker, aren't you?
你简直就是一个小修理匠 不是吗?

285
00:24:55,190 --> 00:24:58,680
What? Is that your name? Tinker?
什么? 这是你的名字? "Tinker(修理匠)"?

286
00:25:01,060 --> 00:25:02,050
Er ...
呃...

287
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:05,130
Bell? Your name is Bell.
铃当? 你叫"Bell"?

288
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:10,490
Tinker? Bell?
叮当

289
00:25:12,470 --> 00:25:16,000
Tinker Bell? Tinker Bell.
叮当? 叮当

290
00:25:17,310 --> 00:25:22,510
What a lovely name! Well, Tinker Bell, my name's Lizzy.
好可爱的名字! 好的 叮当 我叫莉兹

291
00:25:27,020 --> 00:25:29,890
Do all fairies sound the same when they talk?
所有仙子说话的时候都是这种声音吗?

292
00:25:30,460 --> 00:25:33,990
How do you learn to be a fairy? Do you go to fairy school?
你怎么成为一个仙子的? 你读过仙子学校吗?

293
00:25:34,060 --> 00:25:35,050
Lizzy?
莉兹?

294
00:25:36,230 --> 00:25:38,990
Lizzy? Who are you talking to?
莉兹? 你在和谁说话?

295
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,270
My fairy!
我的仙子!

296
00:25:46,340 --> 00:25:50,780
That's nice, dear. Now, I brought you something I think you'll really enjoy.
很好 亲爱的 现在我给你一些东西 我想你会喜欢的

297
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:54,240
These are some of my old field journals.
这些是我以前的野外日志

298
00:25:54,750 --> 00:25:57,240
Now, I picked out the ones I thought would excite you the most.
现在 我挑出来一些 我想这会激励你的

299
00:25:57,350 --> 00:26:01,690
This one on rocks and minerals is particulary interesting
这一本是关于岩石和矿石的 特别有意思

300
00:26:01,890 --> 00:26:06,350
- Is there a field journal about fairies? - Of course not, Lizzy.
- 有关于仙子的野外日志吗? - 当然没有啦 莉兹

301
00:26:06,860 --> 00:26:10,460
Books like this are based on fact and scientific research,
这些书都是基于事实和科学研究的

302
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:14,260
which is the quite the contrary to your little figurines and drawings.
它们和你的这些小雕像和图画完全不同

303
00:26:14,370 --> 00:26:18,430
Well, just because you've never seen a fairy doesn't mean theyre not real.
可是这只说明你没见过仙子 并不表示仙子就不存在

304
00:26:18,540 --> 00:26:24,740
Now, Lizzy, seeing is believing, and without proof, it's just a fairy tale.
好的 莉兹 亲眼目睹当然是可信的 但没有证明 也就只是一个仙子传说

305
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:30,410
Now, here is a blank field journal Now, you're very talented, my darling,
给 这是一本空白的野外日志 亲爱的 你是很有天赋的

306
00:26:30,950 --> 00:26:35,250
and I'm sure you'll be able to fill it with your own scientific research.
我肯定你能够记录你自己的科学研究

307
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:36,720
Yes, Father.
好的 爸爸

308
00:26:39,590 --> 00:26:43,050
Now if only these leaks were just pretend.
要是这些漏水也只是假象 就好了

309
00:26:45,100 --> 00:26:47,570
Tinker Bell, you can come out now.
小叮当 现在你可以出来了

310
00:26:51,410 --> 00:26:57,170
Look, Lizzy, thanks for showing me your collection, but I really should be...
瞧 莉兹 谢谢你让我看你的收藏 但我真的要...

311
00:26:59,310 --> 00:27:00,840
You want to go?
你要走了?

312
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:04,650
Oh. I really wish you'd stay.
噢 我真希望你留下来

313
00:27:05,620 --> 00:27:07,090
I'm sorry, Lizzy.
真抱歉 莉兹

314
00:27:08,320 --> 00:27:10,620
Okay, I understand.
好的 我理解

315
00:27:18,370 --> 00:27:20,490
So, I guess this is goodbye.
那么 我想这就是再见了

316
00:27:25,140 --> 00:27:27,370
What's wrong? Can't you fly in the rain?
怎么了? 你不能在雨中飞吗?

317
00:27:30,540 --> 00:27:33,010
You can stay with me until the rain stops.
在雨停之前你能留在我这里

318
00:27:33,110 --> 00:27:36,510
I'll show you around my room. We can play with my toys.
我会让你参观我的房间 我们还能玩我的玩具

319
00:27:36,620 --> 00:27:38,520
We'll have so much fun.
我们会很愉快的

320
00:27:45,630 --> 00:27:49,490
- We're past the shallows! - Aye Drop the ma nsail!
- 我们过了浅滩了! - 放下主帆!

